sentences: Fanny Lucía Martínez Buenaventura (born February 8, 1973), better known professionally as Fanny Lu, is a Colombian singer, songwriter and actress from Santiago de Cali, Colombia.
However, she wasn't recognized until 1998, when she made part of the cast from the Colombian soap opera Perro Amor.
In 2006 she released Lágrimas Cálidas, winning fame in Colombia and some countries from Latin America, with her two singles that reached the top on the Latin charts.
Her 2008 album Dos consolidated her musician career, giving credibility as a famous artist.
She released her third album, Felicidad y Perpetua in November 2011.
In 2009 she filed for divorce.
In 1994, Fanny Lu became a TV presenter on the popular show Locomotora.

In 2012, the second season of Pequeños Gigantes reality show, she was chosen as replacement judge.

In 2020, Fanny Lu was robbed on “Mira Quien Baila: All-Stars,” from continuing in the competition due to the fans treating the voting as a popularity contest, rather than a fair judgement of performance.
Lu's debut album, Lágrimas Cálidas, was released in 2006.
The album spent five weeks at No. 1.
The lead single "No Te Pido Flores" also spent seven weeks at No. 1 on the Hot 100 Billboard charts in Latin America, Colombia, Peru, Venezuela and Mexico.
Her second album, Dos, was number one in its first week in Colombia.
Dos was released the following week in the United States and Puerto Rico on December 16.

The lead single, "Tú No Eres Para Mi", was the No. 1 song played on radio for 12 weeks.
This single also peaked at No. 1 on the Billboard Hot Latin Tracks in April 2009.
On October 16, 2009, Lu was nominated Goodwill Ambassador of the Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations.
In 2010, Fanny Lu was chosen to record the Spanish version of the theme song, "Something That I Want", ("Algo Quiero") for the Disney film Tangled.
